Package: receptormarker
Type: Package
Title: Analysis and Visualization of Immunological Data
Version: 0.99.0
Date: 2015-05-20
Authors@R: c(
    person("Nikhil", "Haas", email="nikhil@nikhilhaas.com",
           role=c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Chris", "Atterbury", email="chris.atterbury@gmail.com", role="aut"),
    person("Jacob", "Glanville", email="jake@hackbio.com", role="aut"))
Description: Provides functions for executing computations on antibody receptor
    sequences and phenotypic markers. Generates visualizations or data suitable
    for visualizing with web-based libraries such as D3.js. Types of analyses
    available include normalization, clustering, and phylogenetic analysis to
    build phylogenetic trees. Utilizes existing packages to perform many
    analyses, focusing not on novel algorithms but rather on making it easer to
    pipe data into these functions and then generate visualizations.
License: BSD_2_clause + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/nsh87/receptormarker
LazyData: True
Depends: R (>= 3.2.0)
Imports:
    htmlwidgets (>= 0.4),
    htmltools (>= 0.2.6),
    seqinr (>= 3.1),
    ape (>=  3.2),
    XML (>= 3.98-1.2),
